obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46598)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Interpretation clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46598&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act,--`
  line
  line `"officer of police" includes also village-watchman, and`
  line
  line `"cattle" includes also elephants, camels, buffaloes, horses, mares, geldings, ponies, colts, fillies,`
  line `mules, asses, pigs, rams, ewes, sheep, lambs, goats and kids ^1[, and`
  line
  line `^2"local authority" means any body of persons for the time being invested by law with the control`
  line `and administration of any matters within a specified local area, and`
  line
  line `"local fund" means any fund under the control or management of a local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 1 of 1891, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Cf. definition ins. 3 (28) of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), which applies to all Act, passed after the 14 January,`
  line 1887.
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46599)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of pounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46599&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Pounds shall be established at such places as the Magistrate of the`
  line `District, subject to the general control of the State Government, from time to time directs.`
  line
  line `The village by which every pound is to be used shall be determined by the Magistrate of the District.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46600)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Control of pounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46600&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The pounds shall be under`
  line `the control of the Magistrate of the District; and he shall fix, and may from time to time alter, the rates of`
  line `charge for feeding and watering impounded cattle.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46628)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of pound-keepers. Pound-keepers may hold other offices. Pound-keepers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for s. 6.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46628&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Appointment of pound-keepers. Pound-keepers may hold other offices. Pound-keepers to be`
  line `public servants.--The State Government shall appoint a pound-keeper for every pound.`
  line
  line `Any pound-keeper may hold simultaneously any other office under the Government.`
  line
  line `Every pound-keeper shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46602)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `To keep registers and furnish returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46602&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every pound-keeper shall keep such registers and`
  line `furnish such returns as the State Government from time to time directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46603)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `To register seizures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46603&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `When cattle are brought to a pound, the pound-keeper shall enter in his`
  line register,--
  line
  line `(a) the number and description of the animals,`
  line
  line `(b) the day and hour on and at which they were so brought,`
  line
  line `(c) the name and residence of the seizer, and`
  line
  line `(d) the name and residence of the owner, if known,`
  line
  line `and shall give the seizer or his agent a copy of the entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46604)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `To take charge of and feed cattle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46604&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The pound-keeper shall take charge of, feed and water the`
  line `cattle until they are disposed of as hereinafter directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46605)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Cattle damaging land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 "of 1891, s. 3, for "'take them or cause them to be taken without unnecessary delay".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46605&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The cultivator or occupier of any land,`
  line
  line `or any person who has advanced cash for the cultivation of the crop or produce on any land,`
  line
  line `or the vendee or mortgagee of such crop or produce or any part thereof,`
  line
  line `may seize or cause to be seized any cattle trespassing on such land and doing damage thereto or to`
  line `any crop or produce thereon, and ^1[send them or cause them to be sent within twenty-four hours] to the`
  line `pound established for the village in which the land is situate.`
  line
  line `Police to aid seizures.--All officers of police shall, when required, aid in preventing (a) resistance to`
  line `such seizures, and (b) rescues from persons making such seizures.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 10 of Act I of 1871.--In the principal Act, in section 10, after the words and`
  line `figures "the Bombay Village panchayat Act, 1933," the words "or any corresponding law in force in any`
  line `part of the State of Bombay" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 4]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 10, 12 and 26 of, and insertion of new section 28A in Act I of 1871.--In`
  line `the Cattle-trespass Act, 1871--`
  line
  line `(1) in section 10, after the words "or any part thereof the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"or a watch and ward appointed by a panchayat established under the Bombay Village`
  line `Panchayats Act, 1933, or any person authorised by the State Government in this behalf, either by`
  line `name or by virtue of office."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXXIV of 1950, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46606)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Cattle damaging public roads, canals and embankments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46606&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Cattle damaging public roads, canals and embankments.--Persons in charge of public roads,`
  line `pleasure-grounds, plantations, canals, drainage-works, embankments and the like and officers of police,`
  line `may seize or cause to be seized any cattle doing damage to such roads, grounds, plantations, canals, drainage-works, embankments and the like, or the sides or slopes of such roads, canals, drainage-works or`
  line `embankments or found straying thereon,`
  line
  line `and shall ^2[send them or cause them to be sent within twenty-four hours] to the nearest pound.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to the application of s. 11 to forests, see the Indian Forest Act, 1927 (16 of 1927), s. 70; to railways see the Indian Railways`
  line `Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), s. 125 (f).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1891, s. 4, for "take them without unnecessary delay".`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46607)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Fines for cattle impounded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46607&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Fines for cattle impounded.--For every head of cattle impounded as aforesaid, the poundkeepers shall levy a fine in accordance with the scale for the time being prescribed by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette. Different scales may be prescribed for`
  line `different local areas.`
  line
  line `All fines so levied shall be sent to the Magistrate of the District through such; officer as the State`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `List of fines and charges for feeding.--A list of the fines and of the rates of charge for feeding and`
  line `watering cattle shall be posted in a conspicuous place on or near to every pound.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 12A and 12B in Act I of 1871.--In the principal act, after section 12, the`
  line `following new sections shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"12A. Security in respect of impounded cattle. --(1) In any local area to which he state Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, apply this section , every pound-keeper shall, before releasing`
  line `any impounded cattle, require the owner of the impounded cattle or his agent to make, in the form to be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government, a declaration regarding the ownership of such cattle and to deposit`
  line `by way of security such sum as the state Government may, by rules, prescribe, Different scales may be`
  line `prescribed for different areas or different classes of cattle.`
  line
  line `(2) If any cattle belonging to such owner are impounded within a period of six months from the date`
  line `on which the security is deposited, and if the seizure is not adjudged illegal, the amount of deposit or a`
  line `part thereof, as may be directed by the State Government by rules made in this behalf, shall stand`
  line `forefeited to the State Government. If cattle are not impounded as aforesaid, the amount of security`
  line `deposit shall, on an application may by or on behalf of the depositor, be refunded to him on the expiry of`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On every occasion on which the release of the cattle impounded under this Act is claimed, the`
  line `owner of the cattle shall deposit a fresh security.`
  line
  line `12B. Removal of cattle to specified places.--(1) If in any local area to which the State Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette apply this section, a Mamlatdar, Tahsildar, Naib-Tahsildar or`
  line `Mahalkari is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(i) that the grazing land set apart for the use of cattle of one or more village in the taluks, tahsils`
  line `or mahal under his jurisdiction is insufficient for the cattle belonging to the permanent residents of`
  line `such village or villages; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that the crops or grass standing on any agricultural land or grazing land so set apart are likely`
  line `to be damaged by cattle belonging to persons who are not residents of such village or villages and`
  line `who own more than twenty head of cattle,`
  line `he may--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case referred to in clause (i) direct any such resident owner, by special or general order,`
  line `to remove or cause to be removed all or any dry or useless cattle belonging to him to such place or`
  line `places within the State and within such period as may be specified in the order, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any case referred to in clause (ii) direct any such non-resident owner, by special or general`
  line `order, to remove or cause to be removed all or any of his cattle to such place or places within the state`
  line `and within such period as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) If the owner of the cattle fails to remove the cattle as directed under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Mamlatdar, Tahsildar, Naib-Tahsildar or Mahalkari, as the case may be, may direct a police officer not`
  line `below the rank of a head constable to remove or cause to be removed such cattle to the place or places`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Mamlatdar, Tahsildar, Naib-Tahsildar or Mahalkari is satisfied that the order issued by him`
  line `under sub-section (1) is contravened by any owner or keeper of cattle, he may impose a fine not`
  line `exceeding one thousand rupees. Any fine so imposed may, on failure of such owner or keeper to pay the`
  line `same within the specified time, by recovered by sale of all or any of the cattle ordered to be removed`
  line `under sub-section (1)."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 5]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `In section 12,--`
  line
  line `(a) the words "head of" shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "Different scales may be prescribed for different local area" the following`
  line `shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Progressively increasing scales may be prescribed in respect of cattle belonging to or kept by`
  line `the same person according to the number of cattle impounded at a time and the number of times`
  line `such cattle are impounded and different scales may be prescribed for different local areas.";`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act XXXIV of 1950, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 1921, s. 2, for section 12. See section 71 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927 (16 of 1927) under which the State`
  line `Government may fix a different scale of fines for cattle impounded under s, 70 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46608)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Procedure when owner claims the cattle and pays fines and charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46608&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of the`
  line `impounded cattle or his agent appear and claim the cattle, the pound-keeper shall deliver them to him on`
  line `payment of the fines and charges incurred in respect of such cattle.`
  line
  line `The owner or his agent, on taking back the cattle, shall sign a receipt for them in the register kept by`
  line `the pound-keeper.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13 of Act 1 of 1871.--In the principal Act, to the first paragraph of section 13,`
  line `the following shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"and on depositing the amount of security prescribed under section 12A."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46609)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Procedure if cattle be not claimed within a week.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46609&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If the cattle be not claimed within seven`
  line `days from the date of their being impounded, the pound-keeper shall report the fact to the officer in`
  line `charge of the nearest police-station, or to such other officer as the Magistrate of the District appoints in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `Such officer shall thereupon stick up in a conspicuous part of his office a notice stating`
  line
  line `(a) the number and description of the cattle,`
  line
  line `(b) the place where they were seized,`
  line
  line `(c) the place where they are impounded,`
  line
  line `and shall cause proclamation of the same to be made by beat of drum in the village and at the marketplace nearest to the place of seizure.`
  line
  line `If the cattle be not claimed within seven days from the date of the notice, they shall be sold by public`
  line `auction by the said officer, or an officer of his establishment deputed for that purpose, at such place and`
  line `time and subject to such conditions as the Magistrate of the District by general or special order from time`
  line `to time direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if any such cattle are, in the opinion of the Magistrate of the District, not likely to fetch`
  line `a fair price if sold as aforesaid, they may be disposed of in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46610)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Delivery to owner disputing legality of seizure but making deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46610&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If the owner or his agent`
  line `appear and refuse to pay the said fines and expenses, on the ground that the seizure was illegal and that`
  line `the owner is about to make a complaint under section 20, then , upon deposit of the fines and charges`
  line `incurred in respect of the cattle, the to him.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 15 of Act 1 of 1871.---In the principal Act, section 15 shall be renumbered as`
  line `sub-section (1) of that section, and after sub-section (1) as so renumbered, the following new sub-section`
  line `shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) If on any complaint referred to in sub-section (1) the seizure is declared to be lawful, or if the`
  line `owner or his agent fails to make such complaint within a period of four weeks from the date of`
  line `delivery of the cattle to him, the pound keeper of shall require such owner or agent to make a`
  line `declaration and to deposit the amount of security as required by section 12A. If the owner or his agent`
  line `fails to make such declaration or to deposit such amount, the cattle delivered to him under sub-section`
  line `(1) shall be seized for the purpose of section 16."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay XIII of 1959, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46611)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure when owner refuses or omits to pay the fines and expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46611&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the owner or his`
  line `agent appear and refuse or omit to pay or (in the case mentioned in section 15) to deposit the said fines`
  line `and expenses, the cattle, or as many of them as may be necessary, shall be sold by public auction by such`
  line `officer at such place and time, and subject to such conditions, as are referred to in section 14.`
  line
  line `Deduction of fines and expenses.--The fines leviable and the expenses of feeding and watering,`
  line `together with the expenses of sale, if any, shall be deducted from the proceeds of the sale.`
  line
  line `Delivery of unsold cattle and balance of proceeds.--The remaining cattle and the balance of the`
  line `purchase-money, if any, shall be delivered to the owner or his agent, together with an account showing--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of cattle seized,`
  line
  line `(b) the time during which they have been impounded,`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of fines and charges incurred,`
  line
  line `(d) the number of cattle sold,`
  line
  line `(e) the proceeds of sale, and`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which those proceeds have been disposed of.`
  line
  line `Receipts.--The owner or his agent shall give a receipt for the cattle delivered to him and for the`
  line `balance of the purchase-money (if any) paid to him according to such account.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 16 of Act 1 of 1871.--In section 16 of the principal Act, for the first and`
  line `second paragraphs the following new paragraphs shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"If the owner or his agent appears and refuses or omits to pay the said fines and expenses and to`
  line `deposit the said amount of security or (in the case mentioned in section 15) to deposit the said fines,`
  line `expenses and amount of security or to make a declaration as required by section 12A, the cattle or as`
  line `many of them as may be necessary, shall be sold by public auction by such officer, at such place and time,`
  line `and subject to such conditions, as are referred to in section 14, or disposed of in accordance with the`
  line `provisions therein.`
  line
  line `The fines leviable and the expenses of feeding and watering together with the expenses of safe, if any,`
  line `and the amount of security prescribed under section 12A shall be deducted from the proceeds of the sale."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46612)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Disposal of fines, expenses and surplus proceeds of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "dispose of them as hereinafter provided".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46612&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The officer by whom the sale was`
  line `made shall send to the Magistrate of the District the fines so deducted.`
  line
  line `The charges for feeding and watering deducted under section 16 shall be paid over to the poundkeeper, who shall also retain and appropriate all sums received by him on account of such charges under`
  line `section 13.`
  line
  line `The surplus unclaimed proceeds of the sale of cattle shall be sent to the Magistrate of the District,`
  line `who shall hold them in deposit for three months, and, if no claim thereto be preferred and established`
  line `within that period, shall, at its expiry, ^1[be deemed to hold them as part of the revenues of the State.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17 of Act 1 of 1871.--In section 17 of the principal Act, after the second`
  line `paragraph, the following new paragraph shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"The amount of security required under section 12A shall be deposited with the pound-keeper."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46613)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Application of fines and unclaimed proceeds of sale.] Rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46613&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46614)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Officers and pound-keepers not to purchase cattle at sales under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46614&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No officer of police`
  line `or other officer or pound-keeper appointed under the provisions herein contained shall, directly or`
  line `indirectly, purchase any cattle at a sale under this Act.`
  line
  line `Pound-keepers when not to release impounded cattle.--No pound-keeper shall release or deliver`
  line `any impounded cattle otherwise than in accordance with the former part of this Chapter unless such`
  line `release or delivery is ordered by a Magistrate or Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46615)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make complaints.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46615&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Any person whose cattle have been seized under this Act, or`
  line `having been so seized, have been detained in contravention of this Act, may, at any time within ten days`
  line `from the date of the seizure, make a complaint to the Magistrate of the District or any Magistrate`
  line `authorised to receive and try charges without reference by the Magistrate of the District.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46616)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Procedure on complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46616&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The complaint shall be made by the complainant in person or by an`
  line `agent personally acquainted with the circumstances. It may be either in writing or verbal. If it be verbal,`
  line `the substance of it shall be taken down in writing by the Magistrate.`
  line
  line `If the Magistrate, on examining the complainant or his agent, sees reason to believe the complaint to`
  line `be well founded, he shall summon the person complained against, and make an enquiry into the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46617)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Compensation for illegal seizure or detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46617&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If the seizure or detention be adjudged illegal,`
  line `the Magistrate shall award to the complainant, for the loss caused by the seizure or detention, reasonable`
  line `compensation, not exceeding one hundred rupees, to be paid by the person who made the seizure or detained the cattle together with all fines paid and expenses incurred by the complainant in procuring the`
  line `release of the cattle,`
  line
  line `Release of cattle.--and, if the cattle have not been released, the Magistrate shall, besides awarding`
  line `such compensation, order their release and direct that the fines and expenses leviable under this Act shall`
  line `be paid by the person who made the seizure or detained the cattle.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46618)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Recovery of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46618&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The compensation, fines and expenses mentioned in section 22`
  line `may be recovered as if they were fines imposed by the Magistrate.]^1`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See ss. 63 to 70 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and s. 421 of the Cede of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974); cf.`
  line `also. s. 25 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46619)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Penalty for forcibly opposing the seizure of cattle or rescuing the same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46619&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Whoever forcibly`
  line `opposes the seizure of cattle liable to be seized under this Act,`
  line
  line `and whoever rescues the same after seizure, either from a pound, or from any person taking or about`
  line `to take them to a pound, such person being near at hand and acting under the powers conferred by this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be punished with imprisonment for a period not exceeding`
  line `six months, or with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46620)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Recovery of penalty for mischief committed by causing cattle to trespass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46620&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Recovery of penalty for mischief committed by causing cattle to trespass.--Any fine`
  line `imposed 21 ^2[under the next following section or] for the offence of mischief by causing cattle to trespass`
  line `on any land may be recovered by sale of all or any of the cattle by which the trespass was committed,`
  line `whether they were seized in the act of trespassing or not, and whether they are the property of the person`
  line `convicted of the offence, or were only in his charge when the trespass was committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to the application of s. 25 in the case of cattle-trespassing on a railway, see the Indian Railways Act, 1390 (9 of 1890),`
  line `s. 125 (3).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1891, s. 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46621)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Penalty for damage caused to land or crops or public roads by pigs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46621&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any owner or keeper of`
  line `pigs who, through neglect or otherwise, damages or causes or permits to be damaged any land, or any`
  line `crop or produce of land, or any public road, by allowing such pigs to trespass thereon, shall, on conviction`
  line `before a Magistrate, be punished with fine not exceeding ten rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[The ^2[State Government], by notification in the Official Gazette, may from time to time with respect to`
  line `any local area specified in the notification, direct that the foregoing portion of this section shall be read as`
  line `if it had reference to cattle generally, or to cattle of a kind described in the notification, instead of to pigs`
  line `only, or as if the words "fifty rupees" were substituted for the words ten rupees, or as if there were both`
  line `such reference and such substitution.]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Substitution of Section 26.--In the principal Act, for section 26, the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely: --`
  line
  line `"26. Penalty for damage caused to land or crops or public roads or for injury caused to any person by`
  line `cattle or for cattle on public roads.--`
  line
  line `(1) Any owner or keeper or attendant of cattle who through neglect or criminal motive or otherwise`
  line `damages or causes or permits to be damaged any land or any crop or produce of land or any public road`
  line `or anything or causes injury to any person or persons by allowing such cattle to trespass thereon, or lets`
  line `loose any cattle to stray on any public road and thereby causes obstruction to traffic shall, on conviction`
  line `before a judicial magistrate, be punishable with fine which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but`
  line `which may extend to one thousand rupees and in default of payment of fine, simple imprisonment for a term not exceeding one month for the first offence and for the subsequent offences, fine not less than one`
  line `thousand rupees but which may extend to two thousand rupees or to simple imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three months.`
  line
  line `(2) While convicting such person under sub-section (1), the magistrate may order him to pay the`
  line `person whose land, or crop or produce of land or anything has been damaged or the person who is injured,`
  line `such compensation depending upon the value of the loss or expenses so incurred for the medical`
  line `treatment, as may be considered reasonable and in default of payment, the cattle in respect of which the`
  line `offence has been committed shall be forfeited and sold on auction in order to compensate the person so`
  line `aggrieved."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 15 of 2002, s. 2.]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 26A.-- In the principal Act, after section 26, the following new section 26A shall`
  line `be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"26A. Cognizance of offence.--No Court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `section 26 except on a report in writing of the facts constituting such offence made by the person`
  line `aggrieved by such offence or by person who is a public servant as defined in section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code, 1860 (Act 45 of 1860)."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 15 of 2002, s. 3.]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 26 of Act (1 of 1971).--For section 26 of the Cattle Trespass Act, 1871,`
  line `(hereafter called the principal Act), the following shall be substituted--`
  line
  line `"26. Penalty for damage caused to land by cattle.--Any owner, keeper or attendant of cattle, who`
  line `though neglect or otherwise, damages or causes or permits to be damaged any land, or any crop or`
  line `produce of land by allowing such cattle to trespass thereon, shall on conviction before a Magistrate, be liable to a fine not less than Rs. 10 but not exceeding Rs. 250 or to imprisonment for a term not exceeding`
  line `three months or to both."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 7 of 1954, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `In section 26,--`
  line
  line `(a) the first paragraph shall be numbered as sub-section (1) of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (1) so numbered, the following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) The Magistrate trying the offence under sub-section (1) may order,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the accused shall pay such compensation, not exceeding two hundred and fifty`
  line `rupees, as the Magistrate considers reasonable, to any person for any damage proved to have`
  line `been caused to his crop or other produce of land by the accused committing the offence;`
  line
  line `(b) that the pigs in respect of which the offence has been committed shall be forfeited to the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Any compensation awarded under sub-section (2) may be recovered as if it was a fine`
  line `imposed under this section.";`
  line
  line `(c) the second paragraph shall be numbered as sub-section (4) of that section and in`
  line `sub-section (4) so numbered the words "the foregoing portion of" shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXXIV of 1950, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to the application of s. 25 in the case of cattle-trespassing on a railway, see the Indian Railways Act, 1390 (9 of 1890),`
  line `s. 125 (3).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1891, s. 7.`
  line
  line `3. Added by s. 8, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46622)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Penalty on pound-keeper failing to perform duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46622&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any pound-keeper releasing or`
  line `purchasing or delivering cattle contrary to the provisions of section 19, or omitting to provide any`
  line `impounded cattle with sufficient food and water, or failing to perform any of the other duties imposed`
  line `upon him by this Act, shall, over and above any other penalty to which he may be liable, be punished, on`
  line `conviction before a Magistrate, with fine not exceeding fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `Such fines may be recovered by deductions from the pound-keepers salary.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46623)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Application of fines recovered under section 25, 26 or 27.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46623&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `All fines recovered under section`
  line `25, section 26 or section 27 may be appropriated in whole or in part as compensation for loss or damage`
  line `proved to the satisfaction of the convicting Magistrate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `After section 28, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"28A. Offence under section 26 of the be cognizable.--The offence under section 26 shall be`
  line `cognizable."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXXIV of 1950, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46624)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Saving of right to sue for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46624&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Nothing herein contained prohibits any person whose`
  line `crops or other produce of land have been damaged by trespass of cattle from suing for compensation in`
  line `any competent Court.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Substitution of new section 29 for existing section 29 of Act 1 of 1871.--In the principal Act, for`
  line `the existing section 29, the following new section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"29. Saving of right to sue for compensation.--Nothing herein contained prohibits any person`
  line `whose property, crops or other produce of land have been damaged or to whom any hurt or injury or`
  line `obstruction has been caused by trespass of cattle from suing for compensation in any competent`
  line `court."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XIII of 1959, s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46625)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Set-off.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46625&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any compensation paid to such person under this Act by order of the convicting`
  line `Magistrate shall be set-off and deducted from any sum claimed by or awarded to him as compensation in`
  line `such suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46626)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power for State Government to transfer certain functions to local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (b) rep. partially by Act 10 of 1914 and partially by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263&sectionId=46626&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00006_187101_1523268567263
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The StateGovernment may, from time to time by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer to any local authority within any part of the territories under its administration in`
  line `which this Act is in operation, all or any of the functions of the State Government or the Magistrate of`
  line `the District under this Act, within the local area subject to the jurisdiction of the local authority.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 32 after section 31 of Act 1 of 1871.--After section 31 of the principal`
  line `Act, the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"32. Power to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rule for carrying into effect the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular but without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such rules may`
  line `provide for the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the form of, and the procedure relating to, the declaration, and the scales of deposits to be`
  line `made, under section 12A;`
  line
  line `(ii) the procedure regulating the making of security deposits, custody and refund thereof;`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner in which any cattle may be disposed of;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules under this section shall be subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication in the official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules make under this section shall be laid before each house of the Legislature as soon as`
  line `may be after they are made, and shall be subject to such modifications as the State Legislature may`
  line `make during the session in which they are so laid, or the session immediately following."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay XIII of 1959, s. 11iv9563`
